  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6592.77 sitting right between the massive negative gamma wall at 6590 (-14.8B) and positive gamma resistance at 6605 (+14.8B), dealers are in maximum hedging flux as spot ping-pongs between amplifying and stabilizing zones. The breakout regime with -30B total GEX means dealers will aggressively buy any dip toward 6590/6580 and sell rallies into 6605/6600, creating violent two-way volatility in this narrow 15-point range. Watch 6590 as the critical flip level - a break below triggers dealer buying into 6580, while a push above 6605 forces dealer selling that could fuel a melt-up.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect violent whipsaw action between 6590-6605 until one side breaks decisively.",
